					<head>Commentaries</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the books of Daniel, Ezra-Nehemiah and Chronicles (fragments).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="129v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perushim </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרושים</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century  </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The Hebrew text in an Arabic phonetic transcription, with the Arabic translation and commentary by Japheth, is embodied.</p>
								<p>The Hebrew text is provided with the vowel-points and accents in red ink.</p>
								<p>Contains portions of: Daniel 1:3-5, 2:28-30, Ezra 4:23-5:7, 6:6-21, 7:13-28, 8:19-34, 8:36-9:14, 10:26-33, 10:38-44, Nehemiah 1:1-2:8, 8:11-9:6, 9:8-22, 9:32-10:29, 10:31-33, 10:35-11:8, 11:26-12:19, 13:17-31, 1Chronicles 1:1-12, 1:35-48, 11:13-25, 11:32-47, 15:27-16:18, 18:1-19:5, 21:28-22:10, 27:21-24, 28:11-15, 2Chronicles 15:9-16:6.</p>
								<p>Sedarim are marked in the margin in Arabic, with a small pen and ink design (e.g., folio 65v, 124v), mostly cut away.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; a Naskhi hand of 11th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>129 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>216</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>122</height>
										<width>95</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>129 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).  </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>The quires, all of the more or less imperfect, are signed with Arabic numerals on the left-hand upper corner of the first page. Only one such signature has been preserved. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>Lacunae after folios: 12, 21, 31, 45, 48, 61, 115.<p>Gaps after folios 2, 3, 7, 13, 19, 25, 34, 35, 46, 55, 62, 68, 69, 77, 79, 88, 90, 96, 97, 104, 113, 120, 121, 122. </p>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning and at the end. </p>
									<p>Most of the folios are more or less damaged (the best preserved part of the volume being folio 70-113).Modern restoration, stuck on paper. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="12 15" writtenLines="12 15">
									<p>The vowel-points and accents are supplied in red ink. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
